Nigeria men’s senior volleyball team yesterday qualified for the 2019 All Africa Games after defeating Burkina Faso three nil to clinch the first position at the Zone 3 qualifiers held in Abidjan, Cote d’Ivoire. On Monday, the Coach Japhet Nuhu tutored side defeated host Cote d’Ivoire 3-0 to book a place in the finals of the competition. In the gruelling encounter that lasted for 1hour 17minutes, the Nigerian lads stood firm to beat Cote d’Ivoire 25-19, 26-24 and 25-16 for their second win. The Nigerian volleyball had beaten Niger Republic with the same score line in their opening match of the competition on Saturday at the Palais des Sports. The president of the Nigeria volleyball federation, Engineer Musa Nimrod had promised that the men’s volleyball team will deliver the All Africa Games ticket. In his reaction to the team’s qualification yesterday, the president told Daily Trust that he was not surprised by the success recorded by the team in Abidjan. He said “The victory didn’t come to me as a surprise. Even before the team left Nigeria for Abijdan, I told the players that I want not just the ticket but the first position. “I am happy that they succeeded in doing what I charged them to do. I, therefore, commend the players and their officials for doing us proud”. Nimrod therefore said the federation will ensure the team enjoys adequate preparations for the All Africa Games which holds from August 19to 31  in Morocco. AAG Qualifiers: Nigeria men’s volleyball team depart for Abidjan AAG qualifiers: Nimrod charges volleyball team to beat Ivory Coast Team Nigeria in bright start at Nations Beach Volleyball Championships Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin